definition: to decide/to determine/to execute (sb)/(of a dam etc) to breach or burst/definitely/certainly

sentences.english: Similar proposals have failed in New York and Philadelphia .
sentences.chinese: 類似的提案在紐約和費城遭到否決。

sentences.english: Their veto was tantamount to terrorism.
sentences.chinese: 他說這五個國家手中的否決權就等同於恐怖主義。

sentences.english: President Bush says he will veto that proposal.
sentences.chinese: 布什總統說他將否決這個建議。

sentences.english: The U.S. voted against the resolution; Russia abstained.
sentences.chinese: 美國投否決票，俄羅斯棄權。

sentences.english: They have rejected a tax on sodas and sugary drinks.
sentences.chinese: 他們否決了針對碳酸飲料的一項稅收。

sentences.english: The plan was negatived by the committee.
sentences.chinese: 該計劃被委員會否決了。

sentences.english: The administration has signaled it would veto the Smith bill.
sentences.chinese: 政府已經表態將會否決史密斯的提議案。

sentences.english: Delays or outright refusals have been reported for imports permits for alumina (feeder stock for aluminum) .
sentences.chinese: 據報道，進口氧化鋁的許可被拖延或者直接否決。

sentences.english: Boards at all four companies recommended voting against the say-on-pay proposals.
sentences.chinese: 四家公司的董事會都建議投票否決該提案。

sentences.english: Ideals be damned for the President who vetoed the ban on partial-birth abortions.
sentences.chinese: 總統否決成型胎兒流產禁令纔是其受反對的原因。

sentences.english: A rebellious congress overrode the president's veto.
sentences.chinese: 不聽話的國會推翻了總統的否決。

sentences.english: A more likely Congressional response would be to revive the legislation Mr.Bush vetoed.
sentences.chinese: 國會更多的反應是使被布什否決的立法再次復活。

sentences.english: But Mr. Bush is not vetoing all spending that is above his budget .
sentences.chinese: 不過布什並沒有否決所有超出其預算的指出議案。

sentences.english: The suggestion was voted down by large majority.
sentences.chinese: 這項議案被大多數票否決了。
提議被一片嘲笑聲否決。

sentences.english: The  projector is  subject to rejection and may be ejected from the  project.
sentences.chinese: 投影機有遭到否決的傾向並可能被逐出工程。

definition: to remove sb from their post/to dismiss
